OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Buffalo River at Ponca
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Station is located on the Buffalo River at Ponca above the old low water bridge about 100 meters upstream from the Highway 74 Buffalo River Bridge  just upstream from the confluence with Ponca Creek at the northern end of Boxley Valley.  Station is within Buffalo National River and can be found on the Ponca 7.5' USGS quadrangle.  This station coincides with the Buffalo National River routineongoing monitoring station maintained by the National Park Service and referenced by STORET primary number: 05NPS002.  The data stored here were collected in 1989 as part of David Mott's University of Arkansas Master's Thesis entitled: ""Effects of Cattle Pasture Runoff on the Water Chemistry of the Buffalo River; Boxley Valley; Arkansas"" (1990).  All data stored at this station were collected during significant rainfallrunoff events to measure the impact of nonpoint source pollution.  For additional information contact David Mott at Buffalo National River  Resource Management; P.O. Box 1173 Harrison AR 72602 (tel. 5017415443).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/STREAM
